1. Executive Summary
GCoder AI is a lightweight, high-performance web application designed to assist students and developers in real-time code analysis. It leverages the Gemini 3 Flash model to identify syntax/logic errors and provide plain-English explanations, helping users learn why their code broke rather than just providing a patch.

2. User Persona
The Learner: A student (e.g., Engineering student) struggling with C or Python assignments, needing immediate feedback on syntax errors to avoid "black box" solutions.

The Developer: A user needing a quick, "no-bloat" debugger that integrates into their workflow without the overhead of heavy IDE plugins.

3. Functional Requirements
Code Input: A multi-language text area supporting C, Python, Java, JavaScript, Rust, Go, SQL, etc.

Intelligent Analysis: Use Gemini 3 Flash to detect errors and explain solutions in plain English.

Reactive UI: The application theme must dynamically shift (Red for Error, Green for Correct) based on the AI’s diagnosis.

Local History: Ability to persist previous code queries in the browser (LocalStorage).

Markdown Support: Render AI output with code highlighting for readability.

4. Non-Functional Requirements
Performance: API requests must be non-blocking (async/await).

Accessibility: Modern glass-morphism design with high-contrast text.

Security: API keys must never be hardcoded in production or committed to version control.
